Requirements:
To be considered for admission to CSULB, you must meet the following minimum requirements: 
1. Be a high school graduate or equivalent; 
2. Complete the 15-unit comprehensive “A-G” pattern of college preparatory courses; 
3. Earn a qualifying “A-G” grade point average (GPA). 

CSULB is impacted for all undergraduate programs, which means we receive more qualified applications than we can accommodate. Therefore, meeting the minimum CSU requirements does not guarantee admission. Admission is competitive and based on the academic record and preparation of the applicants for that term.
